						               													<description>Trick or Treat: The Aftermath is a game where you and your friends split up all the candy you collected on Halloween! Take turns dividing up your Halloween haul and claim the piles that will score you the most points! As you collect your favorite candies, you'll also gain bonuses and tricky abilities to help you get the tastiest mix at the end of the night!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This roll-and-write game uses an &amp;quot;I Split, You Choose&amp;quot; mechanic and takes around 15 minutes for 1-3 players to enjoy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To setup, give everyone a scoresheet and a writing utensil. Then, pick one of the colors to be your &amp;quot;secret color&amp;quot; and write it on the back of the scoresheet. You will score this color twice during scoring. Now you are ready to roll!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round, one player will roll all six dice and divide them into a number of piles equal to the number of players. Then, starting with the next player, everyone will take a pile of dice, leaving the player who split them up to take the last pile. Everyone then writes the die values from their piles in their matching color column and then starts a new round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when one player has completely filled two columns. All values are then added up, bonuses are counted, and the person with the most points wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
